    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-11-02T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-11-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">663.116/66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-11-02T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 2, 1934—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Your despatch No. 163, October 3, 1934. The Department concurs in your view
                    that on the basis of available evidence you could not appropriately insist that
                    Austrian authorities grant the Vacuum Oil Company a higher import quota for
                    1934.</p>
                <p>Should any additional facts develop that put a different complexion on the case,
                    please keep the Department advised.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile should M. W. Bowen, the Company’s export manager who is in Europe,
                    call, please extend to him any appropriate assistance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
